data.title: Chief Bearheart – Find a Grave Gedenkstätte
data.meta_description: Was he really a Sioux?  Was he truly a chief?  Whoever he was, in the 1930's he was a big draw for young people attending summer camps interested in Indian lore.  He made many rounds in Springfield, Massachusetts as well to ladies' clubs and student groups, teaching Indians ways.  Let's remember the times.  In the...
